doc.previous: A more specialised role of a cargo aircraft is that of transporting fuel in support of other aircraft with more limited flight endurance such as fighters or helicopters Smaller cargo aircraft known as utility are often used to transport military communications equipment as temporary or permanent platforms and in the command role by providing airborne command post or as an air ambulance
